This directory shows how to use Ultraviolet in Rails using a helper module.  To
get started, first install Ultraviolet:

  $ gem install ultraviolet

Then copy app/helpers/uv_helper.rb into your Rails application's app/helpers
directory.

This example shows how to use the helper's code method from a page template:

<html>
  <head><title>Syntax highlighting!</title></head>
  <body>
    <%= code('@items.each {|item| puts item }') %>
  </body>
</html>

